attributes.Long form description: The student grabs the side bars but the instructor tells her to assemble the base frame first so she proceeds to align the first pair of the base frames between each other but she does it in the wrong way so the instructor helps her. Next, the student assembles the second pair of base frames and places them on the table. She grabs the first side bar and inserts it into the base frame, then, he grabs the second side bar and inserts it into the base frame too. She proceeds to assemble the three and the four side bars. Then she grabs the screws and the screwdriver to screw the first side bar to the base frame. She then screws the side bars to the base frame too. Next, the student screws the top part of the side bars. Then, the student grabs the bottom tray and assembles it into the rolling cart. She assembles the first bracket with the help of a bolt and hexagon cap nut. Then she assembles the second bracket. Next, the student grabs the middle tray and slides it into the rolling cart but the instructor tells her to start with the upper tray first so she grabs it and inserts it into the rolling cart. The student proceeds to assemble the third and fourth brackets into the side bars with hexagon cap nuts and bolts. The student lifts the middle tray and tries to align it with the side bars. She proceeds to assemble the fifth and the sixth brackets. The student turns the rolling cart and grabs the first wheel. She starts to unscrew the nut of the wheel but the instructor corrects her. She inserts the first wheel into the base frame and screws it. Then she grabs the second wheel and screws it to the base frame. She grabs the third wheel and screws it to the base frame too. The student grabs the fourth wheel and inserts it into the base frame for screwing it. The student stands the rolling cart and looks that the middle tray is assembled wrong so she tries to align it to the side bars but has a lot of trouble. She assembles the fifth and the sixth brackets with the help of bolts and hexagon cap nuts. The student concludes the task by standing the rolling cart.
